  <abstract>Portrait of Hamilton Love, seated, wearing top hat and tails. See also #2564.</abstract>
  <abstract>Henry Hamilton Love (1875-1922) was a partner in Love, Boyd &amp; Co., wholesale lumber. He married Bessie Mai Davis in Dec. 1901. He was chair of the Nashville board of censorship of moving pictures. He died on 5/2/1922 and his death certificate lists the cause of death as: ""Revolver wound of chest - Suicidal.""</abstract>
